# Frontend Rules

## Component Decisions
- Default to Server Components (no 'use client')
- Add 'use client' only when: using hooks, browser APIs, event handlers, or streaming
- Data fetching in Server Components or TanStack Query — never in useEffect

## File Structure
- One component per file
- Co-locate tests: button.tsx → button.test.tsx
- shadcn components in src/components/ui/ — never edit these manually
- Custom components in src/components/{domain}/

## Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Use cn() from '@/lib/utils' for conditional classes
- Dark mode via Tailwind's dark: prefix — test both modes
- No magic numbers — use Tailwind scale (p-4, not p-[17px])

## The 5 Key Screens (must be polished — demo quality)

### 1. Document Upload (src/components/upload/)
- Drag-and-drop zone accepting: PDF, .md, .txt
- Per-file status: uploading → parsing → chunking → embedded ✓
- Error state per file with actionable message
- Show extracted page/section count after parsing

### 2. Questionnaire (src/components/questionnaire/)
- One question per screen (not a long form)
- Progress: "Step 3 of 8" with progress bar
- Skip button on optional questions
- Answers persist to Zustand immediately, save to Supabase on completion

### 3. Job Input (src/app/(dashboard)/jobs/)
- Large textarea for paste OR URL input
- Scrape URL client-side animation (progress dots)
- Show match score immediately after analysis: color-coded bar
  (< 40: red warning, 40–70: amber proceed, > 70: green full steam)

### 4. Generation View (src/components/generation/)
- Agent timeline on the left (Job Analyst ✓ → Relevancy ✓ → Writing... → QA)
- Streaming CV content on the right — words appear in real time
- Toggle between CV and Cover Letter tabs
- "Edit" button opens inline editor at any point

### 5. Review + Diff (src/components/generation/cv-diff.tsx)
- Side-by-side: Original (left) | Tailored (right)
- Highlight additions in green, removals in red
- "Accept" and "Submit" are separate buttons — user must review
- QA warnings shown as amber banners above the diff

## Loading States
- Skeleton loaders for all async content (never spinner-only)
- Streaming content shows progressive reveal (words appearing), not loading state
- Error states must be human-readable — no raw error messages shown to user

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements: aria-label or visible label
- Keyboard navigable (Tab order must be logical)
- WCAG AA contrast minimum

## Performance
- Images via next/image
- Dynamic import heavy components (diff viewer, PDF preview)
- Route-level code splitting is automatic — don't fight it
